        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The goal is to map the polarization and the magnetic field structure with the highest possible resolution i.e.,  significantly better than our earlier SMA observations which had a resolution 
of 0.6 arcseconds. We have selected Band~6 instead of Band~7 to conduct the observations for the primary 
reason that both IRAS 16293-2422 B and A will be within a field which is one-third the size of the primary beam 
at that frequency. This is shown in Figure 2 of the proposal. 

One important factor to consider is the fact that the sources in this region exhibit proper motions. The coordinates would therefore need to be updated as necessary for the epoch of observations.

</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
